Ninethly, ſhe was of a moſt ſweet and chearfull ſpirit;
                  Chearfulneſs. ſhe did not want her croſſes and trials (and great ones too) yet ſeldom was there a cloud ſeen upon her countenance; the ground Whereof was the inward ſerenitie which ſhe poſſeſt in her own ſpirit, in the ſence of Gods love and her intereſt in Chriſt; of which ſhe had moſt precious Scripture evidence, which was ballaſt to her ſoule in all weathers. Surely the joy of

the Lord was her ſtrength, Nehem. 18.10.
